Note: BUILTIN METHOD DEFINITIONS (Julia Base / Core functions)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Each create_*_method returns the JuliaMethod template for one Base/Core
function with its real positional parameter types and return type. Math
functions take Number and return Number (or a promoted concrete type);
collection mutators take the container plus element and return the
container; predicates return Bool; I/O ops return IO subtypes or Nothing.
These templates seed the dispatch table so resolve_julia_method and
infer_julia_method_call_type operate on accurate signatures.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Delegate to make_julia_method with the function name, a list of parameter
type names, the return type name, and the varargs flag. Type names resolve
to concrete JuliaType records inside make_julia_method.
@End Implementation

